<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-02-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gibbs</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-02-21"><hi rend="italic">February 21,
                                    1879</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 136.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 300, in relation to the decision of the Peruvian Government to pay
                            the claims of the members of the Hydrographic Commission of the Amazon,
                            and to say in reply that I have caused the decision to be communicated
                            to the persons interested. I have no doubt the success of your
                            representations in their favor will be fully appreciated.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. M. Evarts.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>